================================================================================
  RISK MANAGEMENT EXAMPLE
================================================================================

SCENARIO: You bought 100 shares at $100.00
Position value: $10,000.00

Entry Price: $100.00
Stop Loss: 5.0% ($95.00)
Take Profit: 15.0% ($115.00)

Risk/Reward Ratio: 3.0:1

Current Price   % Change     Action     Reason
-----------------------------------------------------------------
$95.00            -5.0%      CLOSE      Hit stop loss - cut losses
$92.00            -8.0%      CLOSE      Hit stop loss - cut losses
$105.00            5.0%      HOLD       Within acceptable range
$115.00           15.0%      CLOSE      Hit take profit - lock in gains
$120.00           20.0%      CLOSE      Hit take profit - lock in gains

================================================================================
  PARAMETER TUNING TIPS
================================================================================

HOW TO ADAPT THIS STRATEGY TO YOUR PORTFOLIO:

STEP 1: Define Your Investment Profile
--------------------------------------------------
  Ask yourself:
  - What's my time horizon? (days, weeks, months, years)
  - How much risk can I tolerate?
  - How often can I monitor positions?
  - What's my portfolio size?
  - What assets am I trading? (stocks, crypto, forex, etc.)

STEP 2: Choose Appropriate MA Periods
--------------------------------------------------
  Day Trading:       5/15, 10/20, 10/30
  Swing Trading:     10/30, 15/45, 20/50
  Position Trading:  20/50, 30/100, 50/150
  Long-term:         50/200, 100/300

STEP 3: Select MA Type Based on Speed Needs
--------------------------------------------------
  SMA: More stable, fewer false signals, better for long-term
  EMA: More responsive, faster signals, better for short-term

STEP 4: Set Position Size Based on Risk Tolerance
--------------------------------------------------
  Conservative:  5-10%  (allows 10-20 positions)
  Moderate:     10-20%  (allows 5-10 positions)
  Aggressive:   20-30%  (allows 3-5 positions)

STEP 5: Configure Stop Loss for Asset Volatility
--------------------------------------------------
  Low volatility (blue chips):     3-5%
  Medium volatility (most stocks): 5-10%
  High volatility (small caps):   10-15%
  Very high volatility (crypto):  15-25%

STEP 6: Set Take Profit at 2-3x Your Stop Loss
--------------------------------------------------
  If stop_loss = 5%, set take_profit = 10-15%
  If stop_loss = 10%, set take_profit = 20-30%
  This ensures favorable risk/reward ratio

STEP 7: Backtest and Refine
--------------------------------------------------
  - Test on historical data
  - Measure: Win rate, average profit/loss, max drawdown
  - Adjust if: Too many signals, too few signals, poor win rate
  - Remember: Past performance doesn't guarantee future results

EXAMPLE TUNING SCENARIOS:
--------------------------------------------------

  Scenario: Too many false signals in ranging market
  Solution: â†‘ Increase MA periods (e.g., 20/50 â†’ 30/100)
           â†‘ Switch from EMA to SMA for smoothing
           â†‘ Add filters (volume, RSI, trend confirmation)

  Scenario: Missing quick reversals
  Solution: â†“ Decrease MA periods (e.g., 50/200 â†’ 20/50)
           â†“ Switch from SMA to EMA for responsiveness
           â†“ Consider dual timeframe strategy

  Scenario: Getting stopped out too often
  Solution: â†‘ Widen stop loss based on ATR or volatility
           â†’ Calculate average swing range for your asset
           â†’ Set stop just beyond normal price fluctuation

  Scenario: Missing profit targets (price reverses before target)
  Solution: â†“ Lower take profit target
           â†’ Use trailing stop instead of fixed target
           â†’ Consider pyramiding (scale out at multiple levels)

ADVANCED ADAPTATIONS:
--------------------------------------------------
  1. Multiple Timeframes:
     - Use longer timeframe (daily) for trend direction
     - Use shorter timeframe (hourly) for entry timing

  2. Volatility-Based Position Sizing (already built-in):
     - Pass volatility parameter to calculate_position_size()
     - Automatically reduces size for volatile assets

  3. Market Regime Filters:
     - Only trade when market is trending (ADX > 25)
     - Avoid trading in ranging markets
     - Add volume confirmation for signals

  4. Portfolio-Level Risk Management:
     - Limit total exposure (e.g., max 50% invested at once)
     - Correlate positions to avoid concentrated risk
     - Use position sizing to balance across sectors


